            <p>Key takeaway: <strong>every previous crash was followed by a recovery that exceeded the previous high.</strong> The question isn't whether crypto will recover — it's whether you'll be positioned when it does.</p>

            <h2>What This Means for Meme Coins and Solana</h2>
            <p>Meme coins on Solana have been hit harder than blue chips. $DKing, $BONK, and $WIF are all down 55-75% from recent highs. But here's the pattern: <strong>meme coins that survive the bear market tend to explode in the next bull run.</strong></p>
            <p>Solana itself remains fundamentally strong — the network is processing over 2,500 TPS with sub-cent fees. If SOL survives at $60-70 support, the ecosystem survives. And with it, the meme coins that have real community traction.</p>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <strong>⚠️ Smart Money Move:</strong> Seasoned investors don't panic during crashes — they accumulate. The best performing meme coins are the ones you bought when everyone else was selling. Dollar-cost averaging into high-conviction plays during the dip is historically the most profitable strategy.
            </div>

