            <h2>What Smart Investors Are Doing Right Now</h2>

            <h3>✅ What They're NOT Doing</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Panic selling at a loss</strong> — Selling during a crash locks in losses. Markets recover.</li>
                <li><strong>Checking prices every 10 minutes</strong> — Emotional check-ins lead to emotional decisions.</li>
                <li><strong>Buying with leverage</strong> — Leverage during high volatility is how accounts get liquidated.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>✅ What They ARE Doing</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Setting limit buy orders</strong> — Target price zones and let the market come to you.</li>
                <li><strong>Dollar-cost averaging</strong> — Fixed amounts at regular intervals removes emotion from the equation.</li>
                <li><strong>Rebalancing to high-conviction assets</strong> — Weeding out weak projects and consolidating into the ones with real staying power.</li>
                <li><strong>Staying liquid on the best exchanges</strong> — When the bottom comes, speed of execution matters.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>The Bottom Line</h2>
            <p>This crash isn't fun. Nobody enjoys watching their portfolio drop 40-60%. But crypto has been through this before — worse, even — and every time, those who stayed rational and accumulated during the panic came out ahead.</p>
            <p>The 2026 crash is driven by macro headwinds and a leverage cascade, not a fundamental failure of crypto technology. Bitcoin's blockchain is still running. Solana is still processing 2,500+ TPS. The meme coin communities are still active.</p>
            <p><strong>The infrastructure is intact. The fear is temporary. The opportunity is now.</strong></p>

